(32161, 2, 1452, 'In this module, participants will learn:\n1.  The risks of driving in bad weather.\n2.  Skid control and safe braking techniques.\n3.  How to avoid a crash in adverse conditions.', 'en', 'US'),
(32162, 2, 1234, 'Adverse Weather', 'en', 'US'),
(32163, 2, 1235, 'Difficult Weather, Difficult Driving', 'en', 'US'),
(32164, 2, 1453, 'When adverse weather strikes, driving conditions can become unpredictable and dangerous. Rain and fog reduce visibility. Heavy winds and slick roads affect steering and make it difficult to control the vehicle. Serious as these factors are, drivers who fail to adjust their driving habits in bad weather pose the greatest risk. Weather-related crashes claim thousands of lives every year in Asia.', 'en', 'US'),
(32165, 2, 1236, 'Water Hazards', 'en', 'US'),
(32166, 2, 1454, 'Moisture is the most common weather factor affecting driver safety. Fog or low-lying mist can severely restrict a drivers view of the road. Besides reducing visibility, rain can cause a vehicle to hydroplane, meaning the tires lose contact with the road surface and glide on water. Large amounts of water, such as a flooded road, diminish the effectiveness of brakes.', 'en', 'US'),
(32167, 2, 1455, 'Even when the sky is clear, natural hazards can create significant dangers for drivers. At some angles, bright sunshine can temporarily blind motorists in traffic. High winds restrict steering ability and can push vehicles off course, particularly large trucks. Crosswinds also create air turbulence when entering or leaving tunnels or other covered areas. Another problem is heat, which can make drivers tired or take a heavy toll on vehicles engines. ', 'en', 'US'),
(32168, 2, 1237, 'Veiled Threats', 'en', 'US'),
(32169, 2, 1238, 'Dangerous Neglect', 'en', 'US'),
(32170, 2, 1456, 'Dangerous weather exposes drivers to hazards that are out of their control, yet some refuse to adjust to the conditions despite the risk. These motorists drive too fast, leave insufficient room around other vehicles, or fail to prepare their vehicles for changes in season. Poor choices make it difficult to drive safely in adverse conditions, and they can leave drivers stranded, injured in a crash or worse. ', 'en', 'US'),
(32171, 2, 2097, 'fog', 'en', 'US'),
(32172, 2, 2096, 'wind', 'en', 'US'),
