(32174, 2, 1239, 'Prepare for the Worst', 'en', 'US'),
(32175, 2, 1457, 'It is best to avoid traveling in bad weather altogether. If you must head out, listen to weather reports, observe conditions around you continuously, and bring an emergency kit that includes:\n Non-perishable food and bottled water.\n Reflective clothing.\n A blanket and extra pair of shoes.\n A first-aid kit and seatbelt cutter.\n Road maps.\n Antifreeze liquid and jumper cables.\n Warning triangles, warning lights or road flares.\n A fire extinguisher.', 'en', 'US'),
