(3010, 2, 3539, 'Why is multitasking impossible?', 'en', 'US'),
(3011, 2, 3556, 'Multitasking cannot be done because your brain is not designed to efficiently juggle two or more tasks at a time. In fact, the term multitasking is not accurate. A more accurate phrase is task switching.', 'en', 'US'),
(3012, 2, 3540, 'Single task focus', 'en', 'US'),
(3013, 2, 3557, 'As a person pursues a single goal, both sides of the brain focus on the task at hand.', 'en', 'US'),
(3014, 2, 3541, 'Adding activities', 'en', 'US'),
(3015, 2, 3558, 'Many people assume that the brain is able to divide its attention to focus on multiple tasks simultaneously.', 'en', 'US'),
(3016, 2, 3542, 'Task switching', 'en', 'US'),
(3017, 2, 3559, 'Instead, the brain rapidly switches focus between the two tasks, with one task being suspended while the other is being focused on.', 'en', 'US'),
(3018, 2, 1623, 'When your brain tries to multitask, it divides its attention to focus on each task simultaneously.', 'en', 'US'),
(3019, 2, 2215, 'TRUE', 'en', 'US'),
(3020, 2, 2216, 'FALSE', 'en', 'US'),
(3021, 2, 3543, 'How does multitasking affect performance?', 'en', 'US'),
(3022, 2, 3560, 'When you try to multitask, each task takes longer to complete, and more errors are made, than if you focused on a single task at a time.', 'en', 'US'),
(3023, 2, 3544, 'Multitasking in action', 'en', 'US'),
(3024, 2, 3561, 'In this example, watch as 2 people complete 2 tasks. Person A will focus on a single task at a time, and Person B will attempt to multitask.', 'en', 'US'),
(3025, 2, 3545, 'Multitasking in action', 'en', 'US'),
(3026, 2, 3562, 'Both participants start Task 1 at the same time.', 'en', 'US'),
(3027, 2, 3546, 'Goal shifting', 'en', 'US'),
(3028, 2, 3563, 'Person B decides to move from one task to another. This is called goal shifting, and it is the first step the brain must take in order to switch tasks.', 'en', 'US'),
(3029, 2, 3547, 'Rule activation', 'en', 'US'),
(3030, 2, 3564, 'Next, the brain turns off the rules for the first task, and turns on the rules it needs to complete the next one. This is called rule activation.', 'en', 'US'),
(3031, 2, 3548, 'The task switches', 'en', 'US'),
(3032, 2, 3565, 'After shifting goals and activating new rules, Person B now begins Task 2. Meanwhile, Person A has not needed these processes.', 'en', 'US'),
(3033, 2, 3549, 'Look at what happened', 'en', 'US'),
(3034, 2, 3566, 'Shifting goals and activating new rules does not take long. If done frequently though, that time adds up, and Person B falls behind.', 'en', 'US'),
