(3592, 2, 3556, 'Multitasking cannot be done because your brain is not designed to efficiently juggle two or more tasks at a time. In fact, the term multitasking is not accurate. A more accurate phrase is task switching.', 'en', 'CA'),
(3593, 2, 3539, 'Why is multitasking impossible?', 'en', 'CA'),
(3594, 2, 3540, 'Single task focus', 'en', 'CA'),
(3595, 2, 3557, 'As a person pursues a single goal, both sides of the brain focus on the task at hand.', 'en', 'CA'),
(3596, 2, 3541, 'Adding activities', 'en', 'CA'),
(3597, 2, 3558, 'Many people assume that the brain is able to divide its attention to focus on multiple tasks simultaneously.', 'en', 'CA'),
(3598, 2, 3559, 'Instead, the brain rapidly switches focus between the two tasks, with one task being suspended while the other is being focused on.', 'en', 'CA'),
(3599, 2, 3542, 'Task switching', 'en', 'CA'),
(3600, 2, 1623, 'When your brain tries to multitask, it divides its attention to focus on each task simultaneously.', 'en', 'CA'),
