(33190, 2, 1485, 'When drivers attempt to multitask, their minds rapidly switch from one activity to another because they can concentrate on only one task at a time. As a result, every time we give our brains another non-driving activity to consider, the risk of a crash increases. Consider this: Taking your eyes off the road for a second at 50 km/h is the same as driving with your eyes closed for nearly 15 meters.', 'en', 'US'),
