(33326, 2, 1477, 'Few driving concerns are as common or as dangerous as fatigue. Tired drivers have slower perception times, have impaired judgment and vision, and pay less attention to the actions of other drivers. In the worst cases, fatigued drivers drift from their lane or drive off the road, ending in serious injury or death. Drowsiness is a factor in many fatal crashes in Asia.', 'en', 'MM'),
(33327, 2, 1476, 'In this module, participants will learn:\n1.  The dangers of fatigued driving.  \n2.  How drowsy driving is impaired driving.\n3.  Techniques to help drivers avoid fatigue-related crashes.', 'en', 'MM'),
