(33492, 2, 535, 'Failure to see another vehicle and obstructed vision are factors in up to 60% of priority-related crashes at controlled intersections.', 'en', 'MM'),
(33493, 2, 1499, 'Common courtesy and the right attitude can go a long way to help you avoid misjudgments that end in a serious crash. This means:\n Giving way to all moving traffic posing risk of a collision.\n Signaling intentions properly when changing lanes or turning.\n Avoiding distractions.\n Planning your route and leaving early to avoid the compulsion to speed.\n Giving way to vehicles requiring special priority, such as emergency vehicles.', 'en', 'MM'),
