(33559, 2, 1283, 'High Traffic Interaction', 'en', 'MM'),
(33560, 2, 1501, 'In an intersection, motorists, cyclists and pedestrians all cross paths at different speeds and from different directions in a tight space. The variety of signs, signals and road markings also can be overwhelming and distracting. The resulting confusion is often deadly: At least 1 out of 5 traffic fatalities occurs at an intersection.', 'en', 'MM'),
(33561, 2, 1284, 'Intersections Are Misunderstood', 'en', 'MM'),
(33562, 2, 2493, 'they can obscure a driver''s view', 'en', 'MM'),
(33563, 2, 1502, 'A four-way intersection with traffic signals is what many people think of as an intersection, but roundabouts, T-junctions, staggered crossings, driveways meeting roads, and crosswalks are all examples as well. Anywhere two or more roads intersect, the crash risk increases.', 'en', 'MM'),
(33564, 2, 1503, 'An intersections hazards are often magnified by factors outside a drivers control. Adverse weather can greatly increase a vehicles stopping distance. Parked vehicles, the landscape and roadwork can obscure sightlines, and other road users may act in unexpected or dangerous ways. Up to 50% of collisions with pedestrians and cyclists, the most vulnerable road users, occur at intersections.', 'en', 'MM'),
(33565, 2, 1285, 'Uncontrollable Hazards', 'en', 'MM'),
(33566, 2, 1286, 'Common Driver Mistakes', 'en', 'MM'),
