(2722, 1054, 2, 'Minimize the Risk', 1),
(2723, 1054, 3, 'A few simple techniques will help keep you and others safe when parking and reversing:\n Signal your intentions.\n Reduce your speed and be patient.\n Park in less busy sections of the parking structure.\n Take your time while backing up.\n', 1),
(2724, 1049, 2, 'Parking Lots and Reversing', 1),
(2725, 1049, 3, 'In this module, participants will learn:\n1.  Parking and backing hazards. \n2.  How to choose a low-risk parking space. \n3.  Defensive parking and reversing strategies.\n', 1),
(2726, 1050, 1, '/media/courses/ddt/PRK/Global/Slides/IMG02.svg', 1),
(2727, 1050, 2, 'Danger Zones', 1),
(2728, 1050, 3, 'Parking lots can be chaotic, dangerous places. Drivers often experience high traffic volume, reduced visibility, limited space to maneuver and a wide range of distractions. Reversing collisions are common in these areas. Up to 32% of backover fatalities and up to 60% of backover injuries occur in parking lots.', 1),
(2729, 1051, 1, '/media/courses/ddt/PRK/Global/Slides/IMG03.svg', 1),
(2730, 1051, 2, 'Crowds of Vulnerable Pedestrians', 1),
(2731, 1051, 3, 'Pedestrians can be unpredictable and impulsive in parking lots. They may be distracted or misjudge traffic speeds, emerge suddenly from between parked vehicles, or make mistakes due to obscured vision. Pedestrians have little to no protection in a crash, so even low-speed collisions can be fatal.', 1),
(2732, 1052, 1, '/media/courses/ddt/PRK/Global/Slides/IMG04.svg', 1),
(2733, 1052, 2, 'Backing Into Trouble', 1),
(2734, 1052, 3, 'Every reversing situation is unique, even if drivers back out of the same place every day. Drivers are relatively inexperienced at reversing compared to driving forward, and vehicles are not designed primarily to travel backwards. The blind zone behind the vehicle, invisible to the driver, can be up to 7 meters long. Dirty or debris-covered windows, stacked packages, lampposts and parked vehicles can obscure the view further. ', 1),
(2735, 1053, 1, '/media/courses/ddt/PRK/Global/Slides/IMG05.svg', 1),
(2736, 1053, 3, 'Drivers mistakes increase the risk in parking lots. These include:\n Driving too fast for the conditions.\n Blocking their view by parking beside large vehicles or other obstructions.\n Improper signaling. \n Reversing without checking behind the vehicle, or using only the mirrors.\n Getting impatient.\n Parking in high-risk areas, such as close to the main entrance, increasing the likelihood of a collision.', 1),
